                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18450407-name-575" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-575" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-575" type="surname" value="TURNER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-575" type="given" value="JAMES BENNETT"></interp>JAMES BENNETT TURNER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am an usher of the Court of Bankruptcy. At half-past nine o'clock in the evening of the 19th of March I was walking down King-street, and at the corner of Queen's Head-yard I heard some one walking behind—I turned round suddenly and observed the prisoner with his hand in my friend Mr. Jarvis's pocket—I saw the handkerchief immediately after on the ground—the prisoner threw it down at the corner of the yard.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner. Q.</hi> Why did not you collar me when you saw it? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> My friend desired him to pick it up, which he refused to do, and I said, "Then you shall go to the station."</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18450407-name-576" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-576" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
